From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0068/N] arguments: auto-bump ObjectAlignmentInBytes to >= HeapWordSize under CHERI

THE bug that capped bootclass loading at 13. Found via instrumentation
in MemAllocator::mem_clear + FieldLayoutBuilder::regular_field_sorting:

  ClassAllocator::initialize mem=0x448e8000 word_size=0 hs=2
    HeapWordSize=16 fill_bytes=18446744073709551584   (= -32 in size_t)

The chain:

  ObjectAlignmentInBytes = 8                     (Java standard default)
  MinObjAlignmentInBytes = 8
  MinObjAlignment        = 8 / HeapWordSize
                         = 8 / 16
                         = 0                     <<-- ZERO under CHERI

  align_object_size(N)   = align_up(N, MinObjAlignment=0)
                         = 0                     <<-- collapses to zero

  FieldLayoutBuilder::regular_field_sorting:
    _info->_instance_size = align_object_size(instance_end / wordSize)
                          = 0                    <<-- every class size 0

  InstanceMirrorKlass::allocate_instance(NULL):
    int size = instance_size(NULL) = size_helper() = 0
    Universe::heap()->class_allocate(this, 0, T)

  MemAllocator::mem_clear:
    Copy::fill_to_aligned_words(mem + hs, _word_size - hs)
                              = fill(mem+32, 0 - 2)
                              = fill(mem+32, SIZE_MAX - 1)
                              = write 16 EB of zeros
                              -> SIGSEGV in memset

Fix: under `__CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__`, if user-set ObjectAlignmentInBytes
is below HeapWordSize, auto-bump it to HeapWordSize. On standard LP64
this is a no-op since HeapWordSize=8 and default is 8.

Empirical result: bootclasses loaded jumped from 13 to **146**. JVM now
crashes at the SIMD post-index immediate guarantee (assembler_aarch64.hpp:2295)
— same kind of fault patch 0059 partially fixed, but more sites
remain exercised by the deeper bootstrap.

This is the single most impactful CHERI patch so far in terms of
classes-loaded delta. Found in a single instrumentation iteration with
fast_iter.sh (~80s per cycle).

Refs: docs/11_stack_trace_class_mirror_allocate.md (root cause analysis)
      docs/10_cheri_seam_scan.md (this site missed by Category A scan
                                   because it's in arguments.cpp, not
                                   memory/ subsystem)

diff --git a/src/hotspot/share/runtime/arguments.cpp b/src/hotspot/share/runtime/arguments.cpp
index 5683e4fe025..f20532ef5cb 100644
--- a/src/hotspot/share/runtime/arguments.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/runtime/arguments.cpp
@@ -1502,6 +1502,15 @@ static void no_shared_spaces(const char* message) {
 void set_object_alignment() {
   // Object alignment.
   assert(is_power_of_2(ObjectAlignmentInBytes), "ObjectAlignmentInBytes must be power of 2");
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+  // CHERI purecap: HeapWord = 16 bytes (cap-sized). MinObjAlignment must be
+  // at least HeapWordSize for align_object_size to produce non-zero results
+  // (otherwise MinObjAlignmentInBytes / HeapWordSize = 8/16 = 0, and every
+  // instance gets _word_size=0 from FieldLayoutBuilder via align_object_size).
+  if (ObjectAlignmentInBytes < (intx)HeapWordSize) {
+    ObjectAlignmentInBytes = (intx)HeapWordSize;
+  }
+#endif
   MinObjAlignmentInBytes     = ObjectAlignmentInBytes;
   assert(MinObjAlignmentInBytes >= HeapWordsPerLong * HeapWordSize, "ObjectAlignmentInBytes value is too small");
   MinObjAlignment            = MinObjAlignmentInBytes / HeapWordSize;
